post_cb({"43007570": {"Id": "43007570", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>Whenever a prvalue is required but a glvalue is given, the glvalue may be converted to a prvalue by <em>lvalue-to-rvalue conversion</em> [conv.lval]. Thus prvalues are fairly general and easily obtained.</p>\n", "LastEditorUserId": "596781", "LastActivityDate": "2017-03-24T19:49:31.387", "Score": "3", "CreationDate": "2017-03-24T19:21:32.943", "ParentId": "43007483", "CommentCount": "1", "OwnerUserId": "596781", "LastEditDate": "2017-03-24T19:49:31.387"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_43007483_43007483_0": {"length": 56, "quality": 0.7466666666666667, "section_id": 6005}}, "n3337": {"so_43007483_43007483_0": {"length": 56, "quality": 0.7466666666666667, "section_id": 5773}}, "n4659": {"so_43007483_43007483_0": {"length": 61, "quality": 0.8133333333333334, "section_id": 7504}}}, "43007483": {"ViewCount": "76", "Body": "<p><a href=\"http://eel.is/c++draft/expr.ref#2\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">[expr.ref]/2</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_43007483_43007483_0\">For the first option (dot) the first expression shall be a glvalue\n  having complete class type. For the second option (arrow) the first\n  expression shall be a <strong>prvalue</strong> having pointer to complete class type.\n  The expression E1-&gt;E2 is converted to the equivalent form (*(E1)).E2;\n  the remainder of [expr.ref] will address only the first option\n  (dot).68 In either case, the id-expression shall name a member of the\n  class or of one of its base classes. [\u2009Note: Because the name of a\n  class is inserted in its class scope (Clause [class]), the name of a\n  class is also considered a nested member of that class. \u2009\u2014\u2009end note\u2009]\n  [\u2009Note: [basic.lookup.classref] describes how names are looked up\n  after the . and -&gt; operators. \u2009\u2014\u2009end note\u2009]</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>In the snippet below, <code>p-&gt;f()</code> is a <em>postfix-expression</em> and <code>p</code> is an lvalue.</p>\n<pre><code>struct A{ void f(){} };\nA *p = new A;\nint main(){\n    p-&gt;f();\n}\n</code></pre>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "43007570", "Title": "Why the prvalue below in [expr.ref]/2?", "CreationDate": "2017-03-24T19:13:52.780", "Id": "43007483", "CommentCount": "0", "LastEditDate": "2017-03-24T19:19:13.713", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "5479741", "LastActivityDate": "2017-03-24T19:49:31.387", "Score": "0", "OwnerUserId": "5479741", "Tags": "<c++><language-lawyer><c++1z>", "AnswerCount": "1"}});